- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with inferring quality metrics for streaming video services over the internet. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video streaming and resolution. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper deals with encrypted traffic. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the deployment of the model in homes. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper does touch on the relationship between internet speed and video streaming quality, which could be considered a societal issue.
